the affrighted wood , And man , the imperious lord of all , thy power
The miser's sordid hopes of pain
my flocks in humble Ascra's plains
The nymphs surround the infant boy
conscious of his fame The sestive choirs their hopes proclaim , While Pan exults with uncouth signs of joy
